            <div>
                <blockquote>
                    <q class="purple">
                        <p>
                            Rather belatedly, but nevertheless most sincerely, I should like to take this opportunity to thank you for the excellent and most professional service which you provided as Toastmaster/Master of ceremonies on the occasion of my 60th Birthday Party held on 21st January 2006 at the Five Lakes Resort
                        </p>
                        <p>Your involvement ensured that the entire evening proceeded most smoothly and I should especially like to thank you for being on hand during the discussions held with the hotel's Event Manager over the misunderstanding of the number of desserts which I had ordered for each guest.</p>
                        <p>As a result of your input, the event Manager admitted on behalf of the hotel that an error had occurred on its part and you were in a position to put at ease those guests who were at risk of not getting a dessert. As you are aware, the issue was resolved satisfactorily to the extent that every guest subsequently appeared to be replete although, needless to say, as I write no formal apology, or indeed recompense, has been forthcoming from the hotel.</p>
                        <p>
                            Since the party, I have received a number of comments, all favourable, from my oldest friends and erstwhile colleagues as to the professionalism which you displayed and I felt that you reached exactly the correct degree of formality required to match the occasion.
